00:22:37,191 --> 00:22:39,391
It's not easy to notice the entire staff.

600
00:22:40,051 --> 00:22:41,191
(Meanwhile...)

601
00:22:41,191 --> 00:22:43,051
Goodness.

602
00:22:43,051 --> 00:22:44,791
(She's making fried eggs with blue eggs.)

603
00:22:45,391 --> 00:22:47,851
(It's all so that they can have a warm dinner.)

604
00:22:48,991 --> 00:22:51,521
- You should leave some for yourselves. - It's okay.

605
00:22:51,521 --> 00:22:53,151
Please keep a few.

606
00:22:53,621 --> 00:22:55,021
- Here. - It's all right.

607
00:22:55,021 --> 00:22:56,891
No, we won't accept it.

608
00:22:56,891 --> 00:22:59,321
- You have a big crew. - It's okay.

609
00:22:59,321 --> 00:23:01,651
- Take this then. - We're good.

610
00:23:01,651 --> 00:23:02,651
Don't forget the salt.

611
00:23:03,751 --> 00:23:05,451
- Take care. - Thank you.

612
00:23:05,451 --> 00:23:06,491
Thank you!

613
00:23:07,251 --> 00:23:09,991
- Make way. - Make way!

614
00:23:10,391 --> 00:23:12,821
I'm worried that we have too much.

615
00:23:12,821 --> 00:23:14,051
(They return to base with a generous amount of food.)

616
00:23:15,191 --> 00:23:17,391
Now it's time for you to have dinner.

617
00:23:17,691 --> 00:23:19,121
I hope your boxes are full.

618
00:23:19,321 --> 00:23:21,721
We were able to feel the generosity...

619
00:23:22,291 --> 00:23:24,321
- and love of the locals. - I agree.

620
00:23:24,321 --> 00:23:26,891
- They wanted to give us more. - Right.

621
00:23:26,891 --> 00:23:28,921
- It was hard saying no. - I know.

622
00:23:28,921 --> 00:23:30,291
I'm happy that...

623
00:23:31,691 --> 00:23:34,151
we were able to write them heartfelt poems.

624
00:23:34,491 --> 00:23:36,321
Even if they didn't have food, I wouldn't care.

625
00:23:36,791 --> 00:23:38,291
I was glad I could give them something.

626
00:23:38,451 --> 00:23:39,921
You gave them something?

627
00:23:39,921 --> 00:23:42,021
I don't even know what I'm saying.

628
00:23:42,021 --> 00:23:43,021
I'm so hungry.

629
00:23:43,621 --> 00:23:45,191
Joon Ho needs to eat something.

630
00:23:45,191 --> 00:23:46,451
I know.

631
00:23:46,451 --> 00:23:47,991
He didn't eat a single meal today.

632
00:23:47,991 --> 00:23:49,421
All right.

633
00:23:49,421 --> 00:23:51,721
Let's see what kind of food you got.

634
00:23:51,721 --> 00:23:54,251
- Joon Ho and Tae Hyun. - We got...

635
00:23:54,251 --> 00:23:55,251
What's that?

636
00:23:56,191 --> 00:23:58,091
This is amazing. We got this at the first try.

637
00:23:58,091 --> 00:23:59,451
- At the first try? - Is it good?

638
00:24:00,021 --> 00:24:01,321
We got jeon.

639
00:24:02,621 --> 00:24:05,521
- Gosh. - We got a good one at the first try.

640
00:24:05,521 --> 00:24:06,551
I can't believe this.

641
00:24:06,551 --> 00:24:08,251
- Jeon? - Is it warm?

642
00:24:08,251 --> 00:24:10,321
I'm not sure if I should let you see this.

643
00:24:10,321 --> 00:24:11,691
Defconn would be very excited.

644
00:24:11,691 --> 00:24:13,151
What? What is it?

645
00:24:13,251 --> 00:24:14,851
- It's pork belly meat. - Gosh.

646
00:24:14,891 --> 00:24:16,251
Pork belly meat?

647
00:24:17,551 --> 00:24:19,321
(When they were at Young Jun and Hyang Soon's house...)

648
00:24:19,321 --> 00:24:20,851
("You never know your luck".)

649
00:24:21,221 --> 00:24:22,251
I should give them pork.

