00:24:29,891 --> 00:24:32,391
We even got a frying pan to cook it.

655
00:24:32,391 --> 00:24:33,451
That's amazing.

656
00:24:33,451 --> 00:24:34,591
Where did they get it?

657
00:24:34,851 --> 00:24:36,051
This is the last one.

658
00:24:36,451 --> 00:24:37,721
When we didn't have enough time,

659
00:24:38,021 --> 00:24:39,951
I told them we didn't have rice and kimchi.

660
00:24:39,951 --> 00:24:41,391
- Did you get soup? - What kind of soup?

661
00:24:41,951 --> 00:24:43,221
It's ramyeon.

662
00:24:43,221 --> 00:24:44,651
- Ramyeon? - She even cooked it for us.

663
00:24:44,691 --> 00:24:46,091
- Ramyeon? - Yes.

664
00:24:46,691 --> 00:24:48,321
It smells great.

665
00:24:49,021 --> 00:24:50,851
Is that it?

666
00:24:50,851 --> 00:24:51,921
- Yes. - We should hurry.

667
00:24:51,921 --> 00:24:53,191
I don't want our ramyeon to get soggy.

668
00:24:54,021 --> 00:24:55,021
It's our turn.

669
00:24:55,291 --> 00:24:57,421
- You have a lot of kimchi. - You'll be excited.

670
00:24:57,621 --> 00:25:00,021
You can eat this with pork belly meat.

671
00:25:00,021 --> 00:25:01,651
- Is it green onion kimchi? - Green onion kimchi.

672
00:25:01,851 --> 00:25:02,991
Look at the color.

673
00:25:02,991 --> 00:25:04,221
It's a lot.

674
00:25:04,991 --> 00:25:07,291
You should have left some for her.

