00:31:49,191 --> 00:31:51,721
It's very sweet.

890
00:31:52,121 --> 00:31:53,791
I love it.

891
00:31:53,791 --> 00:31:56,091
We have to finish all the food.

892
00:31:56,751 --> 00:31:58,021
I love the strawberries.

893
00:31:58,521 --> 00:32:00,491
Thank you for the food.

894
00:32:00,491 --> 00:32:01,591
- Thank you. - Thank you.

895
00:32:01,651 --> 00:32:02,991
Thank you very much.

896
00:32:02,991 --> 00:32:04,091
We really enjoyed it.

897
00:32:07,321 --> 00:32:09,521
(After dinner, they are gathered in the village hall.)

898
00:32:09,521 --> 00:32:12,251
We have six poets here.

899
00:32:12,251 --> 00:32:13,451
We are traveling...

900
00:32:13,451 --> 00:32:14,951
in Hadong with the poets.

901
00:32:14,951 --> 00:32:16,651
- Are we still poets? - Of course.

902
00:32:16,651 --> 00:32:17,721
- Are we still poets? - Yes.

903
00:32:17,721 --> 00:32:18,851
I didn't know that.

904
00:32:19,391 --> 00:32:21,321
So we brought in...

905
00:32:21,321 --> 00:32:24,221
real poets this time.

906
00:32:24,221 --> 00:32:26,321
- Gosh. - You're lying.

907
00:32:26,451 --> 00:32:27,991
I won't fall for that.

908
00:32:27,991 --> 00:32:29,291
Stop it.

909
00:32:29,291 --> 00:32:32,991
Before meeting famous poets,

910
00:32:32,991 --> 00:32:37,551
you will appreciate their poems.

911
00:32:37,551 --> 00:32:38,691
Bring it in.

912
00:32:39,891 --> 00:32:41,291
What's that?

913
00:32:41,921 --> 00:32:43,121
I know what it is.

914
00:32:43,121 --> 00:32:44,521
Is it a children's poem?

915
00:32:45,691 --> 00:32:50,421
(It has cute drawings and poor handwriting.)

916
00:32:51,091 --> 00:32:53,451
(They seem to be children's poems.)

917
00:32:53,951 --> 00:32:55,121
Are these children's poems?

918
00:32:55,121 --> 00:32:56,121
I don't think so.

919
00:32:56,621 --> 00:32:58,221
I think mothers wrote them.

920
00:32:59,021 --> 00:33:00,991
He's right. It'd be children...

921
00:33:00,991 --> 00:33:03,191
or old ladies who just learned Hangul.

922
00:33:03,951 --> 00:33:06,091
(Who on earth wrote those poems?)

923
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:07,451
It looks like children's writing.

924
00:33:07,451 --> 00:33:09,521
I want you to read the poems one by one.

925
00:33:09,521 --> 00:33:13,151
Pooping, can you read out one of the poems?

926
00:33:14,621 --> 00:33:16,921
"I was going to sow beans,"

927
00:33:17,321 --> 00:33:19,221
"but I had to study Hangul..."

928
00:33:20,421 --> 00:33:23,491
"so I came running hurriedly."

929
00:33:23,491 --> 00:33:26,721
"I'll sow the rest later."

930
00:33:27,991 --> 00:33:30,691
"I think pheasants will peck at my poem..."

931
00:33:30,691 --> 00:33:32,851
"as well as my beans."

932
00:33:32,851 --> 00:33:34,151
I know what that means.

933
00:33:34,291 --> 00:33:35,851
Is that a pheasant?

934
00:33:35,851 --> 00:33:37,621
- It is. - It's a pheasant.

935
00:33:37,691 --> 00:33:41,291
It means that a pheasant ate all the beans.

936
00:33:41,291 --> 00:33:43,551
What does the last part mean then?

937
00:33:43,551 --> 00:33:46,091
(What could it possibly mean?)

938
00:33:46,091 --> 00:33:47,751
I think it means "like mine".

939
00:33:47,751 --> 00:33:49,691
"I came running hurriedly" sounds so cute.

940
00:33:49,691 --> 00:33:52,491
- "I came running hurriedly". - To study Hangul.

941
00:33:52,491 --> 00:33:55,451
So she was on her way to learn Hangul.

942
00:33:55,451 --> 00:33:59,251
It looks like she just learned to write.

943
00:33:59,251 --> 00:34:01,291
- Kang Jeom Soon. - Read the next one.

944
00:34:01,291 --> 00:34:03,951
It's by Lee Soon Ja.

945
00:34:03,951 --> 00:34:05,721
Tae Hyun, please read it.

946
00:34:05,721 --> 00:34:06,721
"Lee Soon Ja."

947
00:34:06,721 --> 00:34:10,391
"I planted cucumber and eggplant."

948
00:34:10,391 --> 00:34:12,991
"They grew quickly and bore many fruits."

949
00:34:12,991 --> 00:34:15,121
"I started studying at Jeongdong School..."

950
00:34:15,121 --> 00:34:17,661
"when I was 72 years old."

951
00:34:17,751 --> 00:34:20,821
"I'm very grateful for the two teachers..."

952
00:34:20,821 --> 00:34:23,491
"and I'm going to study diligently."

953
00:34:23,491 --> 00:34:26,691
"If there's a good path I should follow,"

954
00:34:26,691 --> 00:34:29,121
"I will without asking questions."

955
00:34:29,551 --> 00:34:32,891
- It shows her determination. - It's great.

956
00:34:32,991 --> 00:34:35,921
It's a nice illustration. She drew it so well.

957
00:34:35,921 --> 00:34:37,521
Do you see those eggplants?

958
00:34:37,691 --> 00:34:40,321
- She seems to be artistic. - She must be.

959
00:34:40,491 --> 00:34:43,551
We have the last poem here.

960
00:34:43,791 --> 00:34:45,921
- "In the World". - Dong Gu will read it.

961
00:34:45,921 --> 00:34:49,551
"The best words in the world are..."

962
00:34:49,551 --> 00:34:51,851
"from the teachers."

963
00:34:52,021 --> 00:34:54,791
"The best faces in the world are..."

964
00:34:54,791 --> 00:34:56,451
"the smiling faces."

965
00:34:56,851 --> 00:35:00,321
"My face reflected in the mirror smiles."

966
00:35:00,451 --> 00:35:03,661
"My teacher's face is pretty like a flower."

967
00:35:04,321 --> 00:35:08,191
The teacher must be so happy.

968
00:35:08,191 --> 00:35:09,891
She's very loved by her students.

969
00:35:09,891 --> 00:35:12,591
She expressed herself using...

970
00:35:12,591 --> 00:35:14,621
- auditory and visual imagery. - What?

971
00:35:14,621 --> 00:35:16,851
She described faces and sounds.

972
00:35:16,851 --> 00:35:17,891
Pardon?

973
00:35:18,391 --> 00:35:22,391
Let's bring out Jeongdong Village's poets.

974
00:35:22,391 --> 00:35:23,661
Please come out.

